cs.LG, cs.CE, cs.CV, cs.HC, cs.NE 

The paper presents a deep neural network model for predicting ECG abnormalities in short-duration 12-lead ECG recordings. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and human-computer interaction (cs.HC) due to the use of deep neural networks and image analysis techniques. Additionally, it involves clinical outcomes and medical diagnosis, which could fall under the sub-categories of computational biology (cs.CE) and neuroscience (cs.NE).
